The China-Vietnam Military "Peace Rescue-2021" Joint Medical Exercise Successfully Concludes - Xinhua News Agency, Hanoi, December 12 (Zhou Na, Teng Huaigin) On the morning of the 12th, the Chinese participating units in the China-Vietnam military "Peace Rescue-2021" joint medical exercise safely returned to Guangxi, China, marking the successful completion of the 7-day training mission. In this joint exercise, the Chinese and Vietnamese militaries focused on the major issue of humanitarian medical rescue, adhered to the mission of medical care and support, and completed joint medical command, joint on-site rescue, and mass casualty management according to actual combat standards, effectively enhancing the medical support capabilities of both militaries. The exercise's achievements were recognized by both the Chinese and Vietnamese militaries. Ruan Xiongsheng, director of the Vietnamese Exercise Guidance Committee, deputy director and chief of staff of the General Logistics Department of the Vietnam People's Army, said at the closing ceremony that through this exercise, Vietnamese military doctors learned from Chinese military doctors about exercise organization and professional activities, and also saw the Chinese medical and support equipment. The achievements of the exercise demonstrate the professional capabilities of the medical forces of both countries in medical assistance and epidemic prevention and control. Chen Chunming, head of the Chinese Guidance Coordination Group and deputy director of the Health Bureau of the Logistics Support Department of the Central Military Commission, said that this exercise is another pioneering and innovative practice based on the successful joint medical consultation event held in 2018, with significant milestone significance. During the exercise, the People's Liberation Army of China donated medical protective masks, medical protective clothing, rapid nucleic acid testing instruments, and other health and epidemic prevention materials to the People's Army of Vietnam.
